Brazil May See $70 Billion in FDI This Year, Mendes Says

-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 
2011-09-13T20:53:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/brazil-may-see-70-billion-in-fdi-this-year-mendes-says-1-.html
Brazil  may receive as much as $70
billion in foreign direct investment this year, Aldo Mendes, the
bank’s director for monetary policy, said to reporters in
Brasilia.  A central bank press officer, who cannot be named due to
internal policy, later clarified that the bank’s official
forecast remains $55 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Harry Maurer at 
 hmaurer@bloomberg.net  